The entire study area of Tiruchirappalli was divided into grid size of 250 m x 250 m using Arcmap software for extracting the sample points. Similarly,(Zheng et al., 2014) used the method of analysing the correlation trend between LST and impervious surface and Land surface temperature and green surface by dividing the study area into 210mx210m grid. In this study grid size of 250 m x 250 m of 2375 sample points were extracted from the LST imagery and the same sample were applied for extracting the values of NDVI and NDBI to comprehend the pattern associated with LST, NDVI, NDBI,MNDWI,BSI for 2001, 2011, 2021 of April, May and June. It can be understood from the correlation (Fig. 13
                        ) for all three years of April, LST has the strongest negative correlation with NDVI of R² value 0.908 for the latest studied year and strongest positive correlation between LST and NDBI of R² value 0.813 for the year 2021 as compared to 2001 and 2011.Positive correlation was found between LST-NDBI for all three years of May and negative correlation between LST-NDVI (Fig. 14
                        ). Similarly, the month June shows a positive correlation between LST-NDBI with R² value as 0.3413 for the year 2021 as compared to 2001 and 2011 and negative correlation between LST-NDVI (Fig. 15
                        ). It proves that the infrastructure of the city is expanding quickly and transforming natural ground surfaces into impermeable built-up area. Conversion of vegetation cover and soil with concrete and asphalt surface has lower albedo which reduce the evapo-transpiration and soil moisture (Levermore & Cheung, 2012;Mathew et al., 2016;Gupta et al., 2020;Roy et al., 2020) Similarly, numerous studies have examined the relationship between LST and NDVI at various scale and they show a strong inverse correlation (Weng et al., 2004;Sharma & Joshi, 2015;Guha & Govil, 2020). Urban areas with vegetation cover have lower surface temperatures due to evapo-transpiration; reduced incident radiation from shadows cast on the ground, and reduced radiation from pervious surfaces near trees. Tiruchirappalli is experiencing high density of built-up area in central part and the outer rural areas of agricultural fileds, open grounds have also been replaced.

